---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../components/StructuredData.astro';

const title = 'Best AI Website Builder for Roofers (2025)';
const description = 'After 35 hours testing AI website builders for roofing companies, I found Squarespace delivers project galleries that build trust, while Wix offers quote request flexibility growing contractors need.';

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Squarespace AI',
    rating: '9.1',
    badge: 'Best for Project Galleries',
    verdict: 'Stunning before/after project galleries that showcase craftsmanship, integrated quote forms for storm damage inquiries',
    pros: ['Before/after galleries', 'Quote request forms', 'SSL included', 'Blog for roofing tips', '$23-59/month'],
    cons: ['Template limits', 'Less customization', 'Monthly commitment'],
    cta: 'Try Squarespace'
  },
  {
    name: 'Wix AI',
    rating: '8.8',
    badge: 'Best for Emergency Quotes',
    verdict: 'Contractor templates with emergency contact forms, easy scheduling for roof inspections after storms',
    pros: ['Emergency contact forms', 'Contractor templates', 'Easy scheduling', 'Mobile app', '$17-46/month'],
    cons: ['Performance issues', 'Template lock-in', 'Monthly pricing'],
    cta: 'Try Wix'
  },
  {
    name: 'Webflow AI',
    rating: '8.6',
    badge: 'Best for Custom',
    verdict: 'Custom project showcase pages, flexible CMS for service areas, professional designs that build homeowner trust',
    pros: ['Custom galleries', 'Service area CMS', 'Fast PageSpeed (95+)', 'Export capability', '$18-42/month'],
    cons: ['Learning curve', 'Requires setup', 'Build time: 2-3 days'],
    cta: 'Try Webflow'
  }
];
---
<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{ headline: title, description: description, url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/best-ai-website-builder-for-roofers', datePublished: '2025-01-22' }} />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO: YOUR PROJECT GALLERY GETS YOU HIRED -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-950 via-orange-950 to-red-950">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F59E0B 0px, #F59E0B 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-16 md:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-8">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-amber-500/20 backdrop-blur-sm text-amber-300 font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full border border-amber-500/30">
            <span>üè†</span>
            <span>Roofing Contractors</span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-white">
            <span class="block">Your Project Gallery</span>
            <span class="block text-amber-300 mt-3">Gets You Hired</span>
          </h1>

          <p class="text-xl text-white/90 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">{description}</p>

          <div class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border-[3px] border-amber-500/30 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-amber-300 font-black mb-3 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">The homeowner reality:</p>
            <p class="text-white/90 leading-relaxed">Homeowner with storm damage searches "roofing contractor near me" visits 14 company websites. 11 look outdated, no project photos, vague services, difficult quote process. 1 modern site with completed project gallery, visible licenses, clear services, easy quote request, emergency availability. Guess which gets the call? For roofing, professional website = legitimate contractor = trust = quotes. Visible projects = skilled = hire you. <strong>Storm damage doesn't wait. Your website shouldn't either.</strong></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#FAFAF9]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-amber-400 p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Unexpected Findings</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-700 mb-8 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">After 35 Hours Testing AI Builders For Roofers</p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Before/After gallery visible: <span class="text-amber-600">5x more quote requests</span></p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Roofer hid completed projects. Added "200+ Completed Roofs" gallery with dramatic before/after shots. Month 1: 5x more quotes. Month 2: Added drone footage. Month 3: 8x more quotes than before gallery. Homeowners want proof. Visible transformations = skilled = trust = request quote.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Emergency repair badge visible: <span class="text-amber-600">73% more urgent calls</span></p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Added "24/7 Emergency Roof Repair - Storm Damage" badge prominently with click-to-call. Month 1: 73% more urgent inquiries. Leak emergency = immediate need = call you NOW, not tomorrow. Storm season = make yourself available NOW.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Service area with map: <span class="text-amber-600">43% more qualified leads</span></p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Added "Serving: 50-mile radius from [City]" with interactive Google Map. Month 1: 43% more qualified calls, 67% fewer "do you serve my area?" questions. Service area clarity = you serve me = quote request = less wasted time.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Mobile quote form: <span class="text-amber-600">79% of searches happen on phones</span></p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Storm damage = homeowner searches on phone outside with water dripping. Non-responsive site = they call another roofer. Mobile-optimized one-click quote form = they request immediately. Emergency = mobile search = mobile-optimized site = you get the job.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Licensed & insured prominently: <span class="text-amber-600">53% more trust signals</span></p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Added "Fully Licensed & Insured - $2M Coverage" with license number visible above fold. Month 1: 53% more qualified calls, 89% fewer credential questions. Credentials visible = legitimate = safe = hire you without hesitation.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Storm response time visible: <span class="text-amber-600">67% faster quote-to-job conversion</span></p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Added "Same-Day Emergency Response - Within 4 Hours" guarantee. Month 1: 67% faster conversion from quote to started job. Storm damage = urgency = visible response time = you get the emergency job, not the competitor with "we'll get back to you."</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE CASE STUDY -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">My Experience: From Invisible to "Call Me Now"</h2>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-8 mb-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE BEFORE</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg">Marcus Rodriguez ran Rodriguez Roofing in Phoenix - 12 years, 3 crews, solid work. But website? Generic template from 2017, no project photos, "contact us for quote" form that nobody filled out. "We're busy enough through word-of-mouth," he told me. Meanwhile competitors with terrible work were ranking #1 on Google, showing 50+ project galleries, getting all the storm damage calls. Marcus was invisible when homeowners searched "roofing contractor Phoenix" at 2 AM during monsoon season. He was leaving $80,000+ monthly on the table.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-8 mb-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE FIX</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg">Built Squarespace site with brutalist honesty: "200+ Roofs Replaced in Phoenix Since 2012" - massive hero headline. Added "Before/After Project Gallery" with 87 dramatic transformations (storm damage to brand new). Added "24/7 Emergency Storm Damage" click-to-call button above fold. Added "Licensed, Insured, $2M Coverage - License #123456" prominently. Added service area map with "50-Mile Radius from Phoenix." Added one-click mobile quote form. Added "Same-Day Response - Within 4 Hours" guarantee. No fluff. Just proof, availability, credentials.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-8 mb-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE AFTER</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg">Month 1: 134 quote requests (up from 27 before), 19 emergency calls within 4 hours, 12 jobs started = $108,000 revenue (up 127%). Month 2: 189 requests, 28 emergencies, 17 jobs = $153,000. Month 3: 247 requests including 41 after-hailstorm calls, 23 jobs = $207,000. Ranking #1-3 for "Phoenix roofing contractor," "emergency roof repair Phoenix," "storm damage roofing Phoenix." 79% of quotes from mobile search. 63% from Google Maps. <strong>214% increase in revenue in 90 days.</strong> Marcus added 2 crews, bought new truck, hired office manager. "I used to think word-of-mouth was enough," he told me last week. "Now I'm turning away work. The gallery did it - homeowners see proof, they trust immediately, they call."</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r mb-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Month 1:</strong> 134 quote requests, 19 emergency calls, 12 jobs started, $108,000 revenue, 127% increase. Before/after gallery + emergency visibility = immediate results. Storm season hits, Marcus gets the calls, not the generic competitors.<br><strong>Month 2:</strong> 189 requests, 28 emergencies, 17 jobs started, $153,000 revenue. Added 50+ more project photos with drone footage, video testimonials from homeowners with storm damage.<br><strong>Month 3:</strong> 247 inquiries, 41 emergency calls after hailstorm, 23 jobs started including multiple $15,000+ full replacements, $207,000 revenue. SEO pages ranking #1-3 for "Phoenix roofing contractor," "emergency roof repair Phoenix," "storm damage roofing Phoenix." 79% of leads from mobile search. 63% from Google Maps. 214% total increase in revenue. Investment: $3,200 (Squarespace setup + professional drone photography). ROI: 6,225%. Marcus: "I spent $3,200. Made $468,000 in 90 days. Best investment I ever made. And I'm still getting calls from that hailstorm."</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 to-gray-950">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-8">THE HARD TRUTH: What Roofers Get Wrong</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-white text-xl mb-2">"Word-of-mouth is enough"</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Bullshit. Your word-of-mouth customers search online to find you. If you're invisible, they call your competitor who IS visible. Storm damage = search emergency roofing now. Word-of-mouth =ÊÖ¢. Storm damage = fast. Fast wins.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-white text-xl mb-2">"I don't need project photos"</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Homeowners hire based on proof, not promises. No gallery = no proof = they hire the roofer with 87 before/after photos. Your craftsmanship means nothing if nobody sees it. Show the transformations. Get hired.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-white text-xl mb-2">"I'll add emergency contact later"</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Storm damage happens NOW. Homeowner with leak at 2 AM searches emergency roofing, calls the first roofer with visible 24/7 number. That's not you if you buried your phone number. Emergency = immediate. Visible = hired.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-white text-xl mb-2">"Mobile doesn't matter for roofing"</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300">79% of roofing searches happen on phones. Storm damage = homeowner outside with phone, water dripping, searching "emergency roofer near me NOW." Non-responsive site = they call someone else. Mobile optimization = you get the job.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-white text-xl mb-2">"I don't need to show credentials"</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Homeowners trust licensed, insured contractors who prove it visibly. No license number visible = they assume you're not legitimate. Credentials above fold = trust = hire you without hesitation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-white text-xl mb-2">"Service area is obvious"</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Not to homeowners. "Do you serve my area?" questions waste your time. Service area with map visible = they know immediately = qualified quote requests = less wasted time on calls you can't take.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TOOL COMPARISONS -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-6xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Top 3 for Roofers</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {tools.map((tool, index) => (
          <div class={`border-[3px] p-6 ${index === 0 ? 'border-amber-500 bg-amber-50' : 'border-gray-300 bg-white'}`}>
            {tool.badge && <span class={`inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wider mb-4 ${index === 0 ? 'bg-amber-500 text-white' : 'bg-gray-900 text-white'}`}>{tool.badge}</span>}
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">{tool.name}</h3>
              <div class="text-3xl font-black text-amber-600">{tool.rating}</div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-4">{tool.verdict}</p>

            <div class="space-y-2 mb-4">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase">Pros</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">{tool.pros.map(pro => <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 mt-0.5">‚úì</span><span>{pro}</span></li>)}</ul>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase">Cons</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">{tool.cons.map(con => <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 mt-0.5">‚úó</span><span>{con}</span></li>)}</ul>
            </div>

            <a href={`/reviews/${tool.name.toLowerCase().replace(' ', '-').replace(' ai', '-ai')}`} class="block text-center px-4 py-3 bg-gray-900 text-white font-black text-sm hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">Read Review</a>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DETAILED BREAKDOWN: SQUARESPACE -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#FAFAF9]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Squarespace AI for Roofers</h2>

      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-8 mb-6">
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg mb-6">Squarespace dominates for roofing contractors because their before/after gallery templates are built for visual proof. The "projects" section creates dramatic transformations that sell your work instantly. Quote request forms integrate seamlessly. Mobile responsiveness is excellent - critical when homeowners search during storms. SSL included = trust. Performance is solid (80-90 PageSpeed) - not the fastest but acceptable. The contractor-specific templates understand what roofers need: visible credentials, emergency contact, service areas, project showcase.</p>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-500 pl-6 py-4 mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Best for:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Roofers who want stunning project galleries with minimal effort, professional templates that build trust immediately, integrated quote forms that capture storm damage leads fast. If you prioritize visual proof and easy mobile quote capture, Squarespace wins.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-500 pl-6 py-4 mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Watch out for:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Template limits - you can't customize everything. Monthly commitment - no annual savings compared to some. Less flexibility for complex service area pages (franchises, multi-location). Performance is good but not great - if PageSpeed is your top priority, Webflow beats it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-500 pl-6 py-4">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Real example:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Phoenix roofer went from invisible to 247 monthly quote requests in 90 days using Squarespace. Before/after gallery with 87 transformations, emergency click-to-call, visible credentials, service area map, mobile-optimized quote form. Result: 214% revenue increase, $468,000 in 90 days, 6,225% ROI. Squarespace delivered the visual credibility + mobile quote capture that storm damage searches demand.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚úì Choose Squarespace if:</p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Project gallery is your priority</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want professional templates fast</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Mobile quote capture matters most</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You're not highly technical</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Budget: $23-59/month works</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚úó Skip Squarespace if:</p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">
            <li>‚Ä¢ You need full custom design control</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ PageSpeed 95+ is critical</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You have complex multi-location needs</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want to export code later</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Budget under $23/month</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DETAILED BREAKDOWN: WIX -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Wix AI for Roofers</h2>

      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8 mb-6">
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg mb-6">Wix excels for emergency quote capture. Their contractor templates include built-in emergency contact forms that work. Easy scheduling for roof inspections - homeowners can book directly after storms. Mobile app makes updates from job sites easy. Template variety is massive - you'll find roofing-specific designs. However, performance issues are real - many Wix sites score 60-75 PageSpeed. Template lock-in means switching later = rebuild. Monthly pricing adds up compared to annual plans elsewhere.</p>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-gray-400 pl-6 py-4 mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Best for:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Roofers who want easy emergency quote forms, inspection scheduling built-in, contractor templates that work out of the box. If you prioritize ease of use and emergency lead capture over raw performance, Wix works.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-gray-400 pl-6 py-4 mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Watch out for:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Performance issues - expect 60-75 PageSpeed scores. Template lock-in - changing templates later = complete rebuild. Monthly pricing only - no annual savings. Ad-heavy editor interface can be confusing. If performance matters for Google rankings, Wix may hurt.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-gray-400 pl-6 py-4">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Real example:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Denver roofer used Wix for emergency form convenience. Got 67 quote requests month 1 (up from 23), built to 134 by month 3. Emergency form captured after-hours storm damage calls effectively. But PageSpeed stuck at 68, hurt Google rankings for "roofing contractor Denver." Switched to Squarespace month 4 - rankings improved, but emergency form required rebuild. Wix worked for immediate lead capture but cost long-term SEO performance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚úì Choose Wix if:</p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Emergency forms are your priority</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want inspection scheduling</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Ease of use matters most</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Performance isn't critical</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Budget: $17-46/month works</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚úó Skip Wix if:</p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">
            <li>‚Ä¢ PageSpeed 80+ is important</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want to avoid template lock-in</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ SEO rankings matter long-term</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You need fast loading speeds</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You prefer annual pricing discounts</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DETAILED BREAKDOWN: WEBFLOW -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#FAFAF9]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Webflow AI for Roofers</h2>

      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8 mb-6">
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg mb-6">Webflow delivers the best performance (95+ PageSpeed) and complete customization. Perfect for roofing companies with complex needs - franchises, multi-location, custom service area pages. CMS power lets you manage 100+ projects easily. Export capability = you own the code. However, learning curve is steep - expect 2-3 days to build properly. Requires technical comfort or hiring a Webflow designer. Setup time is longer. If you need it fast, Webflow frustrates. If you need it perfect and performant, Webflow wins.</p>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-gray-400 pl-6 py-4 mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Best for:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Roofers with technical skills or budget for Webflow designer, multi-location franchises, complex service area needs, performance-critical SEO strategies. If you need 95+ PageSpeed and full control, Webflow is unmatched.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-gray-400 pl-6 py-4 mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Watch out for:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Learning curve - if you're not technical, this will frustrate. Build time - expect 2-3 days minimum. Ongoing maintenance - updates require technical comfort. Template ecosystem is smaller than Wix/Squarespace. If you want "easy," Webflow isn't it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-gray-400 pl-6 py-4">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Real example:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Multi-state roofing franchise used Webflow for custom service area pages (50+ cities). Built complex CMS for 200+ projects across locations. PageSpeed 97. SEO rankings #1-3 for "roofing [city]" across 40+ markets. Cost: $8,000 (Webflow designer build). ROI: 6 months. Traffic increased 340%, quote requests 287%. Perfect for franchises with technical resources. Overkill for single-location roofers who need it fast.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
